HEADWORD: Xylophagides
<hw>Xy`lo*phag"i*des</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Xylophagous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A tribe
or family of dipterous flies whose larvae live in decayed wood. Some of
the tropical species are very large.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

